[[File:Trial by seven of Duncan the Tall.png|250px|right|thumb|The [[Trial by seven of Duncan the Tall]].]]
{{Quote|Once in a long while, you may get two real highborn shits having a go at each other and one of them might be fool enough to demand a trial by seven. Exactly how it sounds: seven men against seven men.|[[Bronn]]|Justice of the Seven Kingdoms}}
A '''trial by seven''' is a variation of a [[trial by combat]]. Very rarely, after the accused has demanded a trial by combat, he may also demand a &quot;trial by seven&quot;: instead of one man versus one man, two teams of seven men each will fight.
